parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank seam leaks can cause fuel to spill onto the road, creating a fire hazard and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, fuel leaks can lead to engine stalling, difficulty starting the engine, and decreased fuel efficiency.
symptoms: Fuel smell inside or outside the vehicle
fuel leaks onto the ground
difficulty starting the engine
engine stalling
decreased fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty weld in the gas tank can cause fuel leaks, leading to unpleasant odors, fire hazards, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Unbearable fuel smell
especially when the top is not down
indicating a possible leak in the gas tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the muffler and tailpipe can cause loud noises, decreased vehicle performance, and potentially lead to exhaust system leaks, which can be hazardous to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Loud noises from the exhaust system
decreased vehicle performance
possible exhaust leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and splitting of the frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Unusual noises or creaking sounds from the frame
visible cracks or splits in the frame
uneven tire wear
vibrations while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front strut can cause loss of vehicle control, reduced braking performance, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
the front of the vehicle sags or leans
unusual noises are heard from the front suspension
the vehicle has a rough ride
the front strut is leaking fluid.
